<body>
    <form action="/hampi" method="get">
    <div id="nav">
        <form action="/search" method="get">
          <p id="p1">Hampi</p>
         </form>
         <hr style="border-color:black;position:relative;top: 70px;">
         <div id="i1">
            <img id="apimg" src="https://travelikan.com/ezoimgfmt/i0.wp.com/travelikan.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Best-Time-To-Visit-Hampi-Karnataka.jpg?resize=768%2C433&ssl=1&ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb9">
        </div>
        <br><br><br><br><br>
        <div id="i2">
            <h2><strong><center>INFORMATION</center></strong></h2>
            <hr style="width: 950px;height: 1.5px;background-color: black;"><br>
            <p>Hampi or Hampe is a small ancient hamlet in Karnataka and a UNESCO World Heritage Site. It houses the ruins of the Vijayanagar Empire, with almost 500 ancient monuments and temples surrounding this small village. People consider Hampi to be of the best places in Karnataka because of its historical relevance. <br>

                Best Time to Visit- October to March <br>
                Ideal Vacation Duration- 2-4 days <br>
                Average expenses: Starting from ₹25,000 (4 days/3 nights) <br>
                Places to Visit- Lotus Palace, Hampi Bazaar, Virupksha Temple, Lakshmi Narasimha Temple, Elephant Stables <br>
                Things to Do- Take a Coracle ride, see the Monolith Bull and the Big Shivlinga, go rock climbing, visit the Archaeological Museum, go biking riding and cliff jumping. <br>
                </p>
            
        </div>
        <div id="i3">
            <center><h2>WEATHER</h2></center><br>
            <hr style="width: 360px;height: 1.5px;background-color: black;">
            <div class="icon">
            <h1><%=temp%>°C</h1><img src="/day/default.png" alt="" srcset="" id="image">
            </div>
            <h1 class="climate"><%=climate%></h1>
                <h2>Humidity : <%=humidity%>%<br><br>Wind Speed : <%=windspeed%>kmph</h2>
        </div>
        <div id="i4">
            <center><h2>TRANSPORTATION</h2></center><br>
            <hr style="width: 360px;height: 1.5px;background-color: black;"><br>
            <p> <img src="https://img.icons8.com/?size=1x&id=oOAYqE64W2MO&format=png" height="25px" width="25px" alt="">&nbsp;&nbsp;By Air-Nearest Airport is JSW Vidyanagar Airport in Toranagallu, which is 40 km away.  <br><br>
                <img src="https://img.icons8.com/?size=1x&id=d8MqKVWJkyqN&format=png" alt="" height="25px" width="25px">&nbsp;&nbsp; By Train-Hospet Junction is 13 km away from Hampi. <br><br>
                <img src="https://img.icons8.com/?size=1x&id=f42OOoV1ACzO&format=png" alt="" height="25px" width="25px">&nbsp;&nbsp;By Road-You will find buses and cabs from Bengaluru and Hospet.</p>
        </div>
    </form>
    <script>
        
